The claim with the title 'Verifying key claims in SA’s 2018 State Of The Nation address debate ' says “ the debt that is guaranteed by the state in Eskom is r350 billion. In SANRAL, it’s r38.9 billion. In South African Airways, it’s r19.1 billion. In Denel, it’s r1.8 billion. In the Road Accident Fund, it’s r8.5 billion. ”
